com.google.openbidder.api.bidding

Class BidResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.openbidder.api.interceptor.UserResponse<BidResponse>
      • com.google.openbidder.api.bidding.BidResponse

  • public class BidResponse
extends UserResponse<BidResponse>
    Open Bidder bid response. You can build either an OpenRTB response (most methods support this), or the exchange-specific "native" response (using only nativeResponse(), but not both.
    See Also:
    BidInterceptor

      • openRtb

        public final com.google.openrtb.OpenRtb.BidResponse.Builder openRtb()
        Returns:
        The delegate OpenRTB bid response builder.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the response builder was already set to native mode.

      • nativeResponse

        public final <T> T nativeResponse()
        Returns:
        The delegate native response. The returned type depends on the exchange, but it will be a mutable form (for protoc-based response models, it should be a builder).
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the response builder was already set to OpenRTB mode.

      • getResponseMode

        public final BidResponse.ResponseMode getResponseMode()
        Returns the BidResponse.ResponseMode, which tells you which of openRtb() or nativeResponse() can be invoked safely.
